# instructions.md — Project Rules (Google Antigravity)

## Goal

Build a lightweight, secure front-end webapp.
Homepage layout:

- Top: fixed header with menu
- Main hero below: a video (or looping mp4/webm) with text on the left
- Right side: 3 large CTA buttons
- Responsive: desktop + mobile

## Tech Stack (Frontend)

- React + TypeScript
- Build tool: Vite (preferred) or equivalent modern bundler
- Styling: vanilla CSS only
  - Allowed: :has() selector, oklch() colors
  - Prefer CSS variables for tokens (color, spacing, radius)
- No UI framework by default (keep bundle minimal)
  - If components are needed later, prefer small/headless libs, not heavy UI kits. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}

## Non-Goals (for MVP)

- No server-side rendering
- No complex state management library unless proven necessary
- No authentication in MVP
- No database in MVP

---

## Project Structure

- /src
  - /components (pure UI)
  - /pages (Home, later: About, etc.)
  - /styles (global.css + tokens.css)
  - /lib (tiny utilities only)
- Keep components small, composable, and testable.
- Avoid deep nesting.

---

## UI / UX Requirements

### Layout

- Header: accessible nav, visible focus styles
- Hero: two-column desktop, single-column mobile
- Video:
  - Use <video> with `muted autoplay loop playsinline`
  - Provide poster image fallback
  - Respect reduced motion: if `prefers-reduced-motion`, pause animation/limit effects
- Buttons:
  - 3 large CTAs, consistent style, clear labels, keyboard accessible

### Design System

- Define tokens in CSS variables:
  - `--bg`, `--fg`, `--accent`, `--muted`, etc. using oklch()
- Use fluid typography with `clamp()`
- Keep animations subtle and cheap (transform/opacity only)

### Performance

- Lighthouse target: 90+ on Performance on desktop baseline
- Avoid heavy libraries; prefer native browser APIs
- Use `prefers-reduced-motion` for any motion-heavy features

---

## Security Rules (Frontend)

### General

- Assume all external input is untrusted (even URLs).
- Never store secrets in the client (no API keys in JS, no private tokens).
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless absolutely required and sanitized.

### Content Security Policy (CSP)

- Prepare for strict CSP:
  - No inline scripts
  - Avoid inline event handlers
  - Prefer self-hosted assets
- If adding third-party scripts later: document why + scope + integrity approach.

### Dependencies

- Minimize dependencies.
- Only add a library if it clearly reduces complexity without inflating bundle.
- Pin versions; keep `npm audit` clean.
- Avoid abandoned packages.

### External Links

- Always use:
  - `rel="noopener noreferrer"`
  - `target="_blank"` only when needed

---

## Accessibility Rules

- All interactive elements must be keyboard operable
- Visible focus indicator (no removing outline without replacement)
- Provide alt text for meaningful images
- Ensure color contrast (buttons + text) is readable

---

## Testing / Quality Gates

- TypeScript strict mode on
- ESLint + Prettier configured
- CI-ready scripts:
  - `npm run lint`
  - `npm run build`
  - `npm run test` (optional for MVP; add when logic grows)
- No build warnings allowed in main branch

